article.headline: Belmont 78, Alabama St. 42
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Keaton Belcher scored a career-high 17 points and Belmont defeated Alabama State 78-42 on Saturday night. The Bruins (1-3), who never trailed, jumped out to a 10-0 lead on two free throws by Scott Saunders with 14:46 left in the first half. Belcher was 6 of 9 from the field and the Bruins finished with a 50.9 shooting percentage (27 of 53). Mick Hedgepeth tallied 11 points, 10 rebounds and four blocks, and Saunders added 13 points for Belmont. The Bruins, who outscored Alabama State 41-19 in the second half, held the Hornets to 23.2 percent from the field in the game (13 of 56). Belmont outrebounded Alabama State 42-28 with Belcher and Keron Johnson grabbing six boards each. The Hornets were led by Tramayne Moorer with 12 points and Tramaine Butler with 11.
